<!--

    *************************************************************************************
    differential config : 1.3 value for all "maxSpeedratio"
    FWA (front wheel assist) = 0.35 "torqueratio" between front and rear diff (we want about 65% of the torque to the rear axle)
    4WD = 0.5 torque ration between front and rear diff (we want the same torque for both axle)



    *************************************************************************************
    trailer high and low rotLimit adjustment :

    for trailer low, the benchmark trailer = Krampe HalfPipe HP20
    for trailer high, the benchmark trailer = rudolph TDK 301 RP


    *************************************************************************************
    brakes :

    if we know the tractor deceleration (example : DLG test report)
    force = acceleration * mass
    brake force at the wheel = deceleration * mass
    since in the game, the brake force is applied to each wheel and the value in the xml is muliplied by 2 for tractors =>
    value to set in the xml = deceleration * mass / 8

    The DLG result = IRL result, effective deceleration of the vehicle. In our case, the xml value = the brake force at the wheel. We can then set a little higher value => 10% more.
    value to set in the xml = deceleration * mass * 0.14

    example : case ih vestrum. DLG test report = 5.1m/s2 and 5800kg => value to set in the xml file = 5.1*5.8*0.14 = 4.14


    *************************************************************************************
    spring :

    we have to take into account the max possible mass for each axle.
    if only the max permissible load is known, we can estimate :
    front axle max load = 0.42 * max load
    rear axle max load = 0.62 * max load

    a good starting value in the xml = 15 * max axle load

    example : case ih vestrum = 3700kg front and 5500kg rear
    value to set in xml : front = 3.7*15=55 / rear = 5.5*15=82

    *************************************************************************************
    damper :

    the value depends on the "dampingratio" we want to achieve
    0.1 for "hard" tire, 0.2 for "soft" and suspended tire

    good starting values for tractor :
    front = 0.17
    rear = 0.13

    value in the xml = 2 * dampingratio * sqrt(5*spring*max axle load)

    example : case ih vestrum
    value to set in xml : front = 2*0.17*sqrt(5*55*3.7)=10.85 / rear = 2*0.13*sqrt(5*82*5.5)=12.35

-->